1.title: Earl Grey Cream Puffs (Choux Au Craquelin)Oven-baked Chicken with Soy Sauce
1.plot: In this video, I will be showing you how to make Earl Grey Cream Puffs. No one can resist a crispy cream puff that is creamy on the inside and bursts with the aroma of earl grey. Ingredients for the Earl Grey Pastry Cream 2 Earl Grey Tea Bags 250ml Milk 3 Egg Yolks 50g Sugar 25g Cake Flour 200ml Heavy Cream or Double Cream 2Tbsp Sugar Ingredients for the Craquelin 85g Unsalted Butter 100g Sugar 100g Cake Flour Ingredients for the Choux Pastry 2 Eggs 120ml Water 50g Unsalted Butter 2g Salt 75g Cake Flour Recipe for the Earl Grey Cream.

2.title: Trempette à la pizza au pepperoni
2.plot: In this video, I will show you how to make a Pepperoni Pizza Dip. I've never done anything before, but it's delicious and incredible. This dip is perfect for home parties and is even better with crispy bread or crackers.

3.title: No-oven Green Tea Tiramisu
3.plot: In this video, I will show you how to make No-Oven Green Tea Tiramisu. I am aware that tiramisu is layered ladyfingers, but the sponge cake went better with the green tea so I altered the recipe a bit. You also can consider cream cheese as a cheaper alternative to mascarpone. It would have been better with just two layers of bread, because it almost turned out like a cake. However, it was still good and I absolutely adore green tea. It's much simpler with Castella cake, so give it a try.

4.title: Choco Sandwich Cookies with Mint Butter Cream
4.plot: In this video, I will show you how to make Choco Sandwich Cookies With Mint Butter Cream. I bought mint syrup three months ago and I'm finally using it. I'm not a fan of mint flavors, but I wanted to make something different. I bought a whole liter of mint syrup, so you'll find some more mint recipes in the future.

5.title: Tteokbokki epicé à la crème (maecatteok)My favorite homemade pancake recipe
5.plot: In this video, I will show you how to make Tteokbokki Spicy with Cream, also called Maeun Carbonara Tteokbokki in Korean (Tteokbokki carbonora Spicy). Tteokbokki is one of my favorite Korean dishes. \ NI know what the genuine carbonara is and that the name is not my invention, I have slightly recreated menus existing in Korean dinners by what Koreans are more familiar with American cream sauce.

6.title: No-oven Strawberry Cheese Cake
6.plot: In this video, I will show you how to make No-Bake Strawberry Cheese Cake. They are perfectly light and fluffy like mousse.

7.title: Eggs in Hell
7.plot: In this video, I will show you how to make Eggs in Hell. I used some leftover veggies from my fridge, and it came out way better than I expected. It looks awesome and was fantastic with Sriracha hot sauce.

8.title: Spicy Chicken Udon with Pumpkin Cream
8.plot: In this video, I made a spicy stir-fried udon topped with sweet pumpkin cream. The combination of super spicy udon and sweet pumpkin cream is delish. I used the sauce from the famous Korean \"Fire Noodle.

9.title: Panna cotta à la framboise
9.plot: Hi, this is Honeykki. Today's menu is panna cotta topped with raspberry. It was so delish, I devoured them all before I could film the finished shot. LOL. I had to shoot again to show you the finished dish. This is an easy recipe and a perfect summer dessert. It's great even without the raspberries, so give this a try.

10.title: Half-and-half Buchimgae with Makgeolli
10.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

11.title: Macaron broche de sailor moon avec du fromage à la crème au beurre
11.plot: Hi. This is Honeykki. Today, I made Sailor Moon Brooch Macaroon With Cream Cheese Buttercream. I used old almond flour I had at home so the coque didn't come out smooth. But the Sailor Moon Brooch came out cute, so I decided to share it. I used cream cheese buttercream for the filling, and it wasn't too heavy, I loved it.Today's menu is Homemade Pancakes. This is one of my favorite recipes. This pancake is so soft and fluffy, it feels like a cloud.

12.title: Cheese Dakgalbi (Spicy Stir-fried Chicken Topped with Cheese)
12.plot: Today, I made Cheese Dakgalbi. Dakgalbi is a stir-fried dish with marinated chicken, vegetables (I used cabbage, green onion and perilla leaves) and other toppings on an iron pan. It originated from the Chuncheon region and is now enjoyed all over Korea. Give it a try, if you visit Korea. I added udon noodles, and it was great. XD You also can use jjolmyeon (chewy noodles), ramen, or dangmyeon (starch noodles). Make fried rice with the leftover sauce, and you'll love it.

13.title: Bol de riz avec du steak
13.plot: It's very hot these days, isn't it? So, I made a Steak Rice Bowl for an energy boost. Add warm rice and steak cut into bite-sized pieces in a bowl, and top off with sauce. Done. It looks complex, but it is very simple. So try it.

14.title: Hobak-pyeonsu (zucchini dumpling)
14.plot: Today's menu is Hobak-Pyeonsu. \"Pyeonsu\" means summer dumpling. Use a lot of vegetables like zucchini, mushroom, etc. It tastes clean and light. There are many ways of making Hobak-Pyeonsu, but I will be using my mother's recipe.

15.title: Glace au citron pour l'eté
15.plot: Today's menu is the perfect summer dessert: Lemon Ice Cream. The fresh, soft ice cream is great for this scorching summer heat.

16.title: Nutella Banana Ice Cream! Easy and Simple!
16.plot: Today, I made easy and simple Nutella Banana Ice Cream without an ice cream maker. Ingredients 3 Bananas 3Tbsp Nutella 20g Chocolate Chips (*optional) Recipe 1) Cut the banana into bite-sized pieces and freeze. 2) Blend banana and Nutella in a food processor or blender. 3) Mix the (2) and chocolate chips and freeze at least three hours. Enjoy.

17.title: Kong-guksu (cold bean soup with noodles)
17.plot: Today's menu is Kong-Guksu. Kong-Guksu is a cold bean soup with noodles. My recipe is a traditional way. If too cumbersome, you can blend unsweetened soybean milk and tofu. Soybean milk and tofu are bean-based foods.

18.title: Bacon-wrapped hotdogs
18.plot: Today, I made Bacon-Wrapped Hotdogs. Enjoy with beer. Ingredients (2 served) 4 Slices of Bacon 2 Sausages (Hot Dogs) 2 Hot Dog Buns Toppings Onions Pickles Ketchup and Mustard (*optional) Recipe 1) Chop the onion and pickles. 2) Wrap the sausages (hot dogs) with two slices of bacon and fry until golden brown. 3) Place a bacon-wrapped sausage (hot dog) in the bun, top with onions and pickles. Add ketchup and mustard to your preference. Don't add too much sauce.

19.title: Oven-baked Chicken with Soy Sauce
19.plot: Today's menu is a copycat oven-baked chicken inspired by Goobne, the Korean chicken brand. Koreans love to pair fried chicken with beer. We call it \"chimaek.\" Shall we chimaek tonight? This recipe also is included in my book, Honeykki's Delicious Table. Enjoy.

20.title: My Favorite Homemade Pancake Recipe
20.plot: Today's menu is Homemade Pancakes. This is one of my favorite recipes. This pancake is so soft and fluffy, it feels like a cloud.

21.title: Potato Salad Sandwich
21.plot: Let's make Potato Salad Sandwich today. Potatoes are in season, so they are delicious no matter how you cook them. So I made a potato salad sandwich using boiled potatoes. You can add boiled eggs to the salad. So try it.

22.title: Recette simple de choco latte à la menthe et aux oréo
22.plot: Today I made Oreo Mint Choco Latte. I used Andes Mint Chocolate, so the recipe is very simple. It looks very chocolatey, but it feels like you just brushed your teeth. So refreshing. The iced choco latte is delicious on its own. So try it.

23.title: Spaghettis au fromage cuits au four
23.plot: A few days ago, I made pepperoni pizza. Today, I'm making Baked Spaghetti With Cheese using leftover ingredients. I was going to make a simple tomato spaghetti, but I had cheese so I baked it. YOLO. You can make the spaghetti however way you want with what you have. This recipe is not absolute.

24.title: Cheese Rice
24.plot: There was a request in comments (\"Please take Cheese Rice video in high definition\") so - I tried it. It looks a bit - well - it's tasty anyway. You can choose whatever you want for toppings. Ingredients for Sauce (One Person) 1.5 spoon Ketchup 1 spoon Red Pepper Paste 0.5 spoon Sugar 1 bowl Rice 2 spoon Ham or Tuna 1 spoon Sweet Corn 1 fistful of Mozzarella"

25.title: Miyeok-guk (soupe coréenne aux algues et au boeuf)
25.plot: Hello. This is Honeykki. Today, I'm making Miyeok-Guk (seaweed soup), a Korean traditional soup. It is a custom to eat this soup on birthdays and just after giving birth. Thank you for watching my video. Ingredients (3~4 served) 15g Miyeok (Dried Seaweed) 150g Beef (Brisket) 1L Water 2~3Tbsp Sesame Oil 2Tbsp Soy Sauce Salt to taste.

26.title: Scones au café et aux pépites de chocolat
26.plot: Today, I made scones for the first time in a long while. I put coffee in the batter, and it was so great with the coffee aroma.

27.title: Thé vert glacé latte (matcha) aux haricots rouges sucrés
27.plot: Today's menu is Iced Green Tea Latte With Sweet Red Beans. Ingredients 200ml Milk 1.5Tbsp Sugar (or syrup, honey, or to taste) 1Tbsp Green Tea Powder or Matcha Powder 50ml Hot Water Ice Cube 2Tbsp Sweet Red Beans Recipe 1) Add sweet red beans and ice cube into your cup 2) Add green tea powder, sugar and hot water in a small cup and mix until all the lumps are gone. 3) Pour the green tea mixture and milk into a cup. Done.

28.title: Cookies moitié-Moitié
28.plot: Hi. Let's make Half-and-Half Cookies from the last Iced Green Tea Latte With Sweet Red Beans video. I had lot of green tea powder left over, so I made cookies that are half green tea latte and half chocolate chip. I made one cookie with the two different doughs, but you can make them into two separate cookies.

29.title: Cabbage Rolls from 'honokaa Boy' Movie
29.plot: Today's dish is Cabbage Rolls from the movie \"Honokaa Boy.\" This recipe includes chilled rice, as in the movie. The combination of creamy sauce and rolls is super soft and delicious. You can opt for tomato sauce instead of cream sauce. I recommend watching the movie before making it.

30.title: Omelet from 'The Hundred-foot Journey' Movie
30.plot: I'm back with another dish from a movie. Today's movie is \"The Hundred-Foot Journey\" starring Helen Mirren and Manish Dayal. They make an omelet in the movie, and it was SO beautiful. So I made it too.

31.title: Fried Chicken Gizzards
31.plot: Today's menu is Fried Chicken Gizzards. This is super simple so it's really good with drinks. Yeah. Ingredients 300g Chicken Gizzards Milk Salt and Pepper 1/2tsp Curry Powder 3~4Tbsp Flour mixture (I used seasoned flour mix for frying) Batter 1cup Flour mixture (I used seasoned flour mix for frying) 1cup cold water Recipe 1) Rinse the gizzards to clean and cut them 2) Put the gizzards in milk in a bowl and marinate for 30 minutes. 3) Mix the gizzards, salt, pepper, curry powder and flour mixture 4) Dip the seasoned gizzards into the batter and fry.

32.title: Jus de mandarine verte
32.plot: Today's drink is Green Tangerine-Ade. Green tangerines are unripe tangerines that are not yet orange. They taste like somewhere in between a tangerine and lime, so they are great as a tea or a sweet drink.

33.title: Apple Crumble Bars
33.plot: Today, I made Apple Crumble Bars using apples I received for Chuseok. I love crumbles, so I always eat just the crumbles on soboro bread. I made apple crumble bars for those who love crumbles and soboro bread like me. Serve the apple crumble bars cold and enjoy with milk. Much more delicious.

34.title: Gungjung tteokbokki (royal tteokbokki)
34.plot: Today, I made traditional Gungjung Tteokbokki (Royal Tteokbokki). This is said to have been made for the royal family and is typically made with soy sauce instead of gochujang (red pepper paste). If you can't eat spicy food, Gungjung Tteobokki is the way to go.

35.title: Simple pudding à la moutarde
35.plot: Today, I made simple custard pudding. It's very smooth, sweet and delicious. So, try it. I used three egg yolks for a softer pudding that melts in my mouth, but if you want a sturdier pudding that keeps form after flipping, use four egg yolks.

36.title: Ojingeochae bokkeum (poulpe séché épicé sauté) : accompagnement coréen
36.plot: Let's make a banchan Today's menu is Ojingeochae Bokkeum fried dried squid). This is a great, quick side dish to make in bulk and keep in the fridge.

37.title: Grilled Squid with Butter
37.plot: With using leftover stir-fried dried squid and just dried squid, I made an accompaniment to a drink. This is super simple so it's really good with drinks. Tasty side dish. Ingredients 125g Shredded Dried Squid (ojinochae) 1Tbsp Butter 1Tbsp Peanut 1Tbsp Sugar Salt and Pepper.

38.title: Comment faire un toast de rue coréen (cuisine coréenne de rue)
38.plot: Today, I show you how to make Korean Street Toast, which is a favorite Korean street food. These are toasted sandwiches, but they are called toast in Korea. There are many ways to make street toasts. You can use any filling you want. This recipe is not absolute. My favorite combination is omelet, ham, cheese and shredded cabbage. Try it.

39.title: Chips de racine de lotus au fromage
39.plot: Let's make simple Fried Cheesy Lotus Root Chips to go with beer. It's simple, yet addicting. You'll keep reaching for it - and the beer. Ingredients Lotus Root Mozzarella Cheese Diluted Vinegar (2 cups Water, 1Tbsp Vinegar) Recipe 1) Peel and thinly slice the lotus root and soak in diluted vinegar. 2) Pat dry the slices with a kitchen towel. 3) Add slices on a heated pan and sprinkle cheese. Cook until golden. Done.

40.title: Strawberry Sandwich & Strawberry Smoothie
40.plot: Strawberries were quite cheap, so I bought and made a Strawberry Sandwich and Strawberry Smoothie. Fruit sandwiches are much better with whipped cream + custard cream. But - I passed on it - Ingredients for the Strawberry Sandwich Bread 100ml Whip Cream 1Tbsp Sugar 1Tbsp Condensed Milk Strawberries Ingredients for the Strawberry Smoothie Strawberries Yogurt Honey Ice.

41.title: Gorgonzola Pizza with Squid Ink Dough
41.plot: Today, I made Gorgonzola Pizza With Squid Ink Dough. It was so good; it felt like I was eating in a restaurant. Delish AF. Oh, I think it can do with a bit more cheese. I feel I put too little. I used squid ink I bought at the supermarket. It is totally optional. And if you are too lazy even to make the dough, you can use store-bought tortilla.

42.title: Bbq coréen samgyupsal
42.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

43.title: Korean Drama 'A Hungry Woman': Cheese Monte Cristo
43.plot: I made a Cheese Monte Cristo sandwich, which was featured in the Korean web drama \"A Hungry Woman.\" \"A Hungry Woman\" is a drama that highlights Korean food. The heroine is played by Park Hee Bon, my favorite actress. They actually called it \"Cheese Monte Cristo,\" but I think it's more French Toast Grilled Cheese Sandwich. The Korean hot pepper was a total game changer. It cancelled out the greasiness with a bit of heat. Perfect for me. It was really good.

44.title: Pistachio Cream Eclairs
44.plot: Today, I made eclairs with pistachio cream. Pistachio is my favorite eclair flavor. The eclair process is difficult, but you can do it. Good luck.

45.title: 'Winnie the Pooh' Pancake & Green Smoothie
45.plot: I make a smoothie every day, and today, I used a \"Winnie the Pooh\"-shaped pan that I bought last year for making pancakes. This is my first time using the pan but - well - I think I shouldn't have bought this. It's more like a - Pretty Trash ...? Ingredients (for 6 pancakes) 120ml Milk 1 Egg 200g Pancake Mix Toppings: Whipped Cream and Strawberries Ingredients for Smoothie 1 Pack (180ml) Almond Milk or Soy Milk 2 Small Bananas 1/2 Apple and Kale.

46.title: No-oven Cream Cheese Bun: Black Sesame Mochi Bread
46.plot: This is a much-requested no-oven, no-bake recipe. Today, I make Cream Cheese Bun using a sweet rice bun mix (black sesame mochi bread) without an oven. It tasted chewy. I used the glutinous rice flour. Ingredients for the Cream 100g Cream Cheese 25g Powdered Sugar Ingredients for the Batter 250g Sweet Rice Bun Mix (black sesame mochi bread, sesame tapioca bread mix, kkaechal ppang mix) 1 Egg 70ml Water Total cooking time on the pan: 15 minutes. Cook 5 minutes, flip after 5 minutes, again after 2 minutes, then after 3 minutes.

47.title: How to Make Stir-fried Tuna (Chamchi-bokkem) Simple Side Dish
47.plot: Today, I'll make a Stir-Fried Tuna called Chamchi-Bokkem in Korea. It's a very simple recipe. Stir-fried tuna goes well with rice. Ingredients 1 Bell Pepper 1/2 Onion 1 Small Canned Tuna (100~150g) Sauce 1Tbs Gochujang (Red Pepper Paste) 1/2Tbsp Ketchup 1/2Tbsp Starch Syrup or Oligosaccharide Sesame Oil Sesame Seeds.

48.title: Ratatouille inspirée par le film pixar ratatouille
48.plot: I'm back with food from a movie. Today's movie is \"Ratatouille.\" There are many different ways to make ratatouille. Today, I'm following Remy's recipe from the movie. If you are too lazy to do it this way, you can add all the ingredients in a pot and make a stew.

49.title: Crispy chocolate chip cookies
49.plot: Today I'll be making Crispy Chocolate Chip Cookies. Enjoy it with coffee or milk. Ingredients (8~9 servings) 140g Unsalted Butter 100g Black Sugar or Brown Sugar 3g Salt 200g Cake Flour 5g Baking Powder 1 Egg, Vanilla Extract 100g Chocolate Chips 60g Nut (30g Almond, 30g Pistachio)

51.title: Du film petite forêt: hiver & printemps, chapati & curry au poulet
51.plot: I'm going to make Chapati and Chicken Curry, which was introduced in the movie \"Little Forest: Winter/Spring.\" Chapati is a flat bread from India. I cooked it in the grill just like the movie and it was funny that swallowed inside the grill.

52.title: Idées de gâteau halloween
52.plot: Today video's is Halloween Cake Ideas using store-bought pie snack. I used chocolate pie snack, but you can use castella or muffin. Actually, I think that failed at it. But so many people said the cakes were cute on Instagram, so here it is. Have a nice weekend.
